Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with energy-efficient user access control and resource allocation in heterogeneous cellular networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves optimization problems related to resource allocation and transmission schemes, which are closely related to information theory. 
3. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper involves the selection of the base station with minimal energy consumption, which can be modeled as a game-theoretic problem. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper involves the optimization of energy consumption in a system with multiple components, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper characterizes the effect of non-ideal power amplifiers on the total energy consumption of different transmission schemes, which is related to multimedia applications.
